<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF9FFE7E1AD00CCFB57FF72" box="[151,1268,150,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF9FFE7E1AD00CCFB57FF72" blockId="1.[151,1436,150,681]" box="[151,1268,150,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<heading id="083581CAFFF9FFE7E1AD00CCFB57FF72" bold="true" box="[151,1268,150,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" reason="1">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E1AD00CCFB57FF72" bold="true" box="[151,1268,150,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Identification of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E06400CDFE72FF72" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1893" box="[350,465,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E06400CDFE72FF72" bold="true" box="[350,465,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E33700CDFD26FF72" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[525,645,150,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E33700CDFD26FF72" bold="true" box="[525,645,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on underside wing morphology and antennae
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF9FFE7E1FD00E1FB4CFD6A" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF9FFE7E1FD00E1FB4CFD6A" blockId="1.[151,1436,150,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Identification of individual museum specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E3D000E1FC96FF17" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1893" box="[746,821,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E3D000E1FC96FF17" box="[746,821,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E25F00E1FC15FF16" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[869,950,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E25F00E1FC15FF16" box="[869,950,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may never be achieved with 100% accuracy; although there are morphological features to accommodate identification in many cases, accurate identification requires an examination of their respective late instar larvae. However, the shape of the submarginal markings on the wing undersides and the tips of the antenna usually provides a very good indication of species, particularly when there is a series of 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFF9FFE7E05A0111FE61FEA6" box="[352,450,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">syntypes</typeStatus>
from the same population, taken at the same time (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E52B0111FB4DFEA6" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1041,1262,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga, 2011</bibRefCitation>
: appendix only; 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E1AD0135FED3FE4A" author="Russell, P. J. C. &amp; Bartolozzi, L. &amp; Hawkins, R. L. &amp; Tennent, W. J. &amp; Leger, T." box="[151,368,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="449 - 472" refId="ref10659" refString="Russell, P. J. C., Bartolozzi, L. Hawkins, R. L., Tennent, W. J. &amp; Leger, T. (2020) Designation of lectotypes for some Spanish and other western European Melitaea taxa, some with mixed syntypic series of M. phoebe ([Denis &amp; Schiffermuller], 1775) and M. ornata Christoph, 1893 (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). SHILAP Revista de lepidopterologia, 48, 449 - 472." type="journal article" year="2020">
Russell 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E1C80135FE87FE4A" box="[242,292,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). These differences can be seen on figures 1–4, which show the undersides of male specimens from two sympatric and partially synchronic populations of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E27701C9FC63FE6F" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1893" box="[845,960,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E27701C9FC63FE6F" box="[845,960,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E2C601C9FBD6FE6E" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[1020,1141,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E2C601C9FBD6FE6E" box="[1020,1141,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Southern Urals, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF9FFE7E1AD01EDFED1FE12" box="[151,370,439,465]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
and females from similar populations near Rakitovec, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF9FFE7E2D501EDFBF6FE12" box="[1007,1109,439,465]" name="Slovenia" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
. Identifications of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E41401EDFA3FFE12" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1326,1436,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E41401EDFA3FFE12" box="[1326,1436,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E1FC0181FE25FE36" authorityName=", Gross &amp; Ebert" authorityYear="1975" box="[198,390,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E1FC0181FE25FE36" box="[198,390,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were based solely on morphometric measurements of genitalia and the biochemical results of 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E1AD01A5FEF0FDDA" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[151,339,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E1E801A5FEA1FDDA" box="[210,258,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. (2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E06701A5FE36FDDA" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J." box="[349,405,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="106 - 115" refId="ref11405" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J. (2016) Long-term survival and diversification of an endemic Melitaea species in mountains of Iran and adjacent areas. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 54 (2), 106 - 115. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12122" type="journal article" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E08C01A5FE50FDDA" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Verovnik, R. &amp; Wahlberg, N. &amp; Varadi, A. &amp; Bereczki, J." box="[438,499,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="267 - 281" refId="ref11547" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, Z., Verovnik, R., Wahlberg, N., Varadi, A. &amp; Bereczki, J. (2017) Mito-nuclear discordance helps to reveal the phylogeographic patterns of Melitaea ornata (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 121, 267 - 281. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / biolinnean / blw 037" type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). DNA analysis has confirmed the specific status of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E50B01A5FB3FFDDA" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1073,1180,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E50B01A5FB3FFDDA" box="[1073,1180,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is widely regarded as a tool for the reliable separation of closely related species. However, it is not definitive, as exemplified by the similarity of the results of the analysis of the 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E3B4021DFD1DFDA2" box="[654,702,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">COI</emphasis>
gene in 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E226021DFC2FFDA3" authorityName="Christoph" authorityYear="1893" box="[796,908,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E226021DFC2FFDA3" box="[796,908,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E2F8021DFB94FDA2" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[962,1079,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E2F8021DFB94FDA2" box="[962,1079,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from western populations. Also DNA analysis has so far been unable to separate 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E3940231FC80FD46" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[686,803,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E3940231FC80FD46" box="[686,803,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF9FFE7E25F0231FB28FD46" authority="Alpheraky, 1881" authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[869,1163,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E25F0231FC6EFD46" box="[869,973,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. sibina</emphasis>
Alphéraky, 1881
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E5A20231FA34FD46" author="Lukhtanov, V. A. &amp; Sourakov, A. &amp; Zakharov, E. V. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N." box="[1176,1431,619,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="1302 - 1310" refId="ref10220" refString="Lukhtanov, V. A., Sourakov, A., Zakharov, E. V. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N. (2009) DNA barcoding Central Asian butterflies: increasing geographical dimension does not significantly reduce the success of species identification. Molecular Ecology Resources, 9, 1302 - 1310. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1755 - 0998.2009.02577. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Lukhtanov 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E4230231FAEAFD46" box="[1305,1353,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
., 2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E1AD02D5FE23FD6A" author="Leneveu J. &amp; Chichvarkhin, A. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[151,384,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="346 - 361" refId="ref10155" refString="Leneveu J., Chichvarkhin, A. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2009) Varying rates of diversification in the genus Melitaea (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae) during the past 20 million years. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 97, 346 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.2009.01208. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Leneveu 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E1C502D5FE94FD6A" box="[255,311,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF9FFE7E0B102D5FDE1FD6A" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[395,578,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF9FFE7E0FD02D5FE5CFD6A" box="[455,511,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), whilst differences in their wing morphology are distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
